{"id": "EUVD-2025-201235", "enisaUuid": "e1761134-53f8-3f36-a1ee-c7e0f7b772aa", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nhwmon: (cgbc-hwmon) Add missing NULL check after devm_kzalloc()\n\nThe driver allocates memory for sensor data using devm_kzalloc(), but\ndid not check if the allocation succeeded. In case of memory allocation\nfailure, dereferencing the NULL pointer would lead to a kernel crash.\n\nAdd a NULL pointer check and return -ENOMEM to handle allocation failure\nproperly.", "datePublished": "2025-12-04T15:31:16", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-04T15:31:16", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/240b82b86a091c1aa49d951d4467425420a081a0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a09a5aa8bf258ddc99a22c30f17fe304b96b5350", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40224"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40224"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2b7eb9c9-ba03-3b0e-a64a-41fbb02ee5a6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.15"}, {"id": "853d0ab6-2920-30eb-90a6-65eb75d25cb9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "9639a12b-a499-3d86-b31e-4fe86e58dde4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "08ebc9def79fc0c4dbb6ecc39263006e3f98b750 <240b82b86a091c1aa49d951d4467425420a081a0"}, {"id": "9cbac851-5662-36b5-8b8f-56eadf53fcba", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "08ebc9def79fc0c4dbb6ecc39263006e3f98b750 <a09a5aa8bf258ddc99a22c30f17fe304b96b5350"}, {"id": "bd8258d3-e81f-32bb-b1bb-2bff55743a72", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "c929beba-f5b5-352d-8e0a-24b746dbc3bb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.6"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "fd84f868-7357-316b-b4e3-36f9e77e9244", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}